_header: Most noble prince our sovereign lord
Subjects: pageant verses; occasional verse; Henry VII
_description: Pageant verses for Henry VII in A.D. 1486 at Bristol — three stanzas rhyme royal

BLCottJulBXII.First Lines:
Moost noble prynce and souueraigne hege lordeTo this poore towne of
                    Bristow that is youre…
BLCottJulBXII.Last Lines:
…To withstonde thoo thing[is] that bee conturiousAnd to doo
                    that may please god moost glorious
BLCottJulBXII.Note: Folio number reflects the most recent foliation.
